<br>
&quot;A strand of hair from a High Elf maiden, Salis' Writ page 90, make sure its the faded page! If its faded, what possible use can it be?!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Do you always talk to yourself Jarven? Trying to frighten the spirits away?&quot;, a voice snickered.<br>
<br>
Jarven recoils in surprise, obviously caught off guard. He could feel his cheeks flush, embareassed to be caught muttering to himself. &quot;Do not mock me woman! I am on a very important mission for Master Ulns!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Of course you are!&quot;, the voice giggled. &quot;Master Ulns always sends young warriors on important missions! Alone, no less. I pray you remembered to bring your sword this time Jarven?&quot; By this time the voice was laughing uncontrollably.<br>
<br>
Jarven sighed as he watched his childhood friend Lesayne stumble from the nearby bushes. &quot;Master Ulns has finally trusted me with a mission all my own. This is important to me Les!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, yes&quot;, Les replied. &quot;Of course it is. Thats why I am here! You didn't think I would let you do this mission without me did you? Now help me up! What kind of gentleman leaves a beautiful young elf on the ground!&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uquillionthegnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quillion the Gnome</A> at: 12/22/01 9:52:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uquillionthegnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quillion the Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/23/01 1:43:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: And so it begins...</span><hr size=1> Jarven pulls Lesayne to her feet. Jarven is always surprised by how light Lesayne is, even in her leather armor. &quot;Doesn't the word 'alone' mean anything to you?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ya, it means by yourself. Which in your case is certain disaster. So here I am!&quot;, Lesayne smirked.<br>
<br>
&quot;but..&quot;, Jarven retorted.<br>
<br>
&quot;Never argue with an elf,silly human.&quot;, Lesayne interupted. &quot; We live about 10 times as long as you do so don't think I can't wait out a disagreement!&quot;<br>
<br>
Jarven sighed. One of those heavy sighs he usually did around Lesayne. Lesayne threw her arm around Jarven and laughed. &quot;Don't worry dear friend. One day I'll let you win an arguement!&quot;<br>
<br>
It didnt take long before Jarven was glad for Lesayne's company. Lesayne was a young druid. Skilled in the ways of survival and privy to the secrets of the forest. Not to mention having someone to talk with on this long journey. &quot;A strand of hair from a High Elf maiden, Salis' Writ page 90, make sure its the faded page! And a coin from Mr. Findlepizz. Those are the three items I must bring back for Master Ulns.&quot;, explained Jarven.<br>
<br>
&quot;He made you memorize the list? He wouldnt write it down?&quot;, asked Lesayne.<br>
<br>
&quot;He was afraid I'd lose the list..&quot;, grumbled Jarven. Jarven glanced over at Lesayne, waiting for her sharp tongued remark. He froze as he noticed Lesayne had stopped a few feet behind him, a concerned look on her face. Lesayne slowly moved her hand to her scimitar and motioned to Jarven to follow her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Something really smelly is approaching.&quot; explained Lesayne. &quot;Best be ready for the worse Jarven.&quot;<br>
<br>
Jarven drew his sword and hid beside Lesayne. He could smell it now too. The unmistakable stench of orcs. He clutched his sword tightly as the sounds of the orcs footfalls grew louder and louder. Jarven could see five of them. Two of the orcs were carrying something on their shoulders. A pole, suspended from their pole was a large bag filled with whatever prize these foul creatures had claimed.<br>
<br>
Jarven's body tensed, ready for combat. As the orcs drew closer and closer Jarven felt Lesayne's hand on his arm. &quot;Hold&quot;, she whispered. &quot;Something's wrong.&quot;<br>
<br>
As the orcs passed Jarven and Lesayne, Jarven realized why Lesayne was so concerned. Jarven could hear muffled sounds coming from the large bag. Crying, he thought to himself. There's a child crying inside that bag!<br>
